'''St. Joseph<U+2019>s Church''', Sarfaraz Rafiqui Road, is the oldest church of the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Lahore]] in Pakistan. It was blessed on October 31, 1853. St. Joseph's was originally built to serve Catholics in the British Army.

The parish of 5,000 families consists of approximately 25,000  Christians.<ref>{{cite web |title = Daily Times November 1, 2003| url= http://www.dailytimes.com.pk/default.asp?page=story_1-11-2003_pg7_14}}</ref>
A Christian and Muslim Peace Committee helps to keep the peace and harmony among the communities. Special days, festivals and other holidays are celebrated together. The committee arranges medical camps, social programmes and awareness programmes. This group also helps to find jobs for unemployed Christians.<ref>{{cite web |title =St. Joseph<U+2019>s Church| url=  http://www.archdioceselahore.org/sjp.html}}</ref>

Archbishop [[Lawrence Saldanha]] used the occasion to make a call for the government to create an independent Minorities Commission with judicial powers. Currently there is no forum for minority grievances to be addressed.

Schools in St Joseph<U+2019>s parish currently educate 3,500 in an effort to reduce the estimated 30-40 percent of parish children who receive no schooling at all.<ref>{{cite web |title = Daily Times October 31, 2003| url= http://www.dailytimes.com.pk/default.asp?page=story_31-10-2003_pg7_12}}</ref>

After being ordained as the new Bishop of Faisalabad on November 1, Bishop [[Joseph Arshad]] performed his first mass in St. Joseph's Church on 3 November 2013. He completed his schooling from
St Joseph<U+2019>s High School in the Parish. <ref>[http://www.dailytimes.com.pk/default.asp?page=2013%5C11%5C04%5Cstory_4-11-2013_pg7_6 Daily Times, November 4, 2013]</ref>

